<h1>News</h1>

<a href="newsarchive.jsp">View The News Archive</a> 

	<h2>A Change to the Forums</h2>
	
	The EQ dev team has always been committed to receiving player input and returning deserved feedback.  However, with as much traffic as the forums have been receiving in recent months, it became increasingly more difficult to properly address each valid player concern.  In an effort to refocus the process, the forums have gone through a rather big change, with a few more changes on the way.  Please visit the current forums and read <a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/ubb/everquest/Forum1/HTML/000001.html" target="new">Absor's initial post</a> first.  He explains just what is happening and why.<br>
<br>
As a side note, please do not flood the EQ Webmaster with emails concerning this change.  The EQ Webmaster is not involved with the forums at all.  There is a form within the forums themselves for you to submit your feedback to the dev team.

